TEXT.0: This enhanced CDF master was generated by NSSDC, with input from R. Fitzenreiter and A. F.-Vinas, to make useable a bare-bones CDF data set provided earlier to NSSDC. This current CDF master version, Oct. 5, 2007, is used for making a new CDF by selecting only certain variables from those available in the original bare-bones CDF (SPHE-00414).

PI_name.0: K. Ogilvie, R. Fitzenreiter, & A. Vinas

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Electron density at 0.5 sec resolution (60-deg sector) taken during one spin.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Electron density is obtained 6 times during a spacecraft spin period. The six measurements are separately averaged to make the six elements of this array. We still need to know the delta t from Epoch to the first of these 6 densities.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Electron Temperature = 1/3 trace of the diagonalized pressure tensor.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Electron Temperatue is 1/3 trace of diagonalized pressure tensor. Electron Temperature = (1/3) (parallel temp + two perpendicular eigenvalues)

VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: Normalized difference between perp. eigenvalues of pressure tensor

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Norm. Gytotropy made by dividing by Electron Temperature

VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: Cos Angle(Press Tensor Princ. Axis, B vector)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Cosine of the angle between pressure tensor principal axis and magnetic field
Eigenvalues of diagonalized pressure tensor divided by (density * Boltzmann constant)

VarAttributes.FIELDNAM: Highest, mid, and lowest energy electron channels above SC potential

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Hi, mid, & lowest energy electron channels > SC potential, used in moments.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Highest is channel 1, lowest is given by value of variable INSET, and mid is given by (INSET+1)/2, dropping any remainder.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Number of energy channels above spacecraft potential
